a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">differential analyzer</a><span>, one of=
 the first operational computing mechanisms. Bush was an ardent proponent o=
f deeptech as a means of winning the war because he saw first-hand the </sp=
an><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/5b58a269-667d-4602-864a-c83a232=
876ed?u=3D16283549" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: unde=
rline;">shortcomings</a><span> of government and academic research after WW=
I as the Dean of Engineering and VP of MIT. Before Germany invaded Poland, =
he left his post to establish a national emphasis on research in Washington=
, DC as the Director of the National Advisory Committee on Aeronautics. Aft=
er the invasion, the urgency of his mission became more apparent. Bush took=
 on the prodigious task of convincing President Franklin Delano Roosevelt t=
o invest in science, not just weapons of mass destruction, but the endless =
frontier that would hold the keys to a </span><em>sustainable</em><span> vi=
ctory. Surprisingly, it worked.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a;=
 font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">In 1940, the Natio=
nal Defense Research Committee was created to boost defense industries. Abo=
